  "chapter": {
    "number": 32,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Righteous King"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, a king will reign in righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and princes will rule with justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Each will be like a shelter from the wind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a refuge from the storm,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like streams of water in a dry land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the shadow of a great rock in an arid land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the eyes of those who see will no longer be closed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the ears of those who hear will listen.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The mind of the rash will know and understand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the stammering tongue will speak clearly and fluently.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No longer will a fool be called noble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor a scoundrel be respected.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For a fool speaks foolishness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his mind plots iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He practices ungodliness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and speaks falsely about the LORD;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he leaves the hungry empty",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and deprives the thirsty of drink.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The weapons of the scoundrel are destructive;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he hatches plots to destroy the poor with lies,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even when the plea of the needy is just.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But a noble man makes honorable plans;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he stands up for worthy causes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Women of Jerusalem"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Stand up, you complacent women;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "listen to me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Give ear to my word,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you overconfident daughters.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a little more than a year you will tremble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O secure ones.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the grape harvest will fail",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fruit harvest will not arrive.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shudder, you ladies of leisure;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "tremble, you daughters of complacency.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Strip yourselves bare",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and put sackcloth around your waists.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat your breasts for the pleasant fields,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the fruitful vines,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and for the land of my people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "overgrown with thorns and briers—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even for every house of merriment",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in this city of revelry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the palace will be forsaken,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the busy city abandoned.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The hill",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2618
          },
          {
            "text": "and the watchtower will become caves forever—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the delight of wild donkeys",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and a pasture for flocks—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "until the Spirit is poured out",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "upon us from on high.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Then the desert will be an orchard,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the orchard will seem like a forest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then justice will inhabit the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness will dwell in the fertile field.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The work of righteousness will be peace;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the service of righteousness will be quiet confidence forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then my people will dwell in a peaceful place,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in safe and secure places of rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But hail will level the forest,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the city will sink to the depths.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed are those who sow beside abundant waters,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who let the ox and donkey range freely.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
